      "type": "elementBody",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Wayfinding is the design of orientation under uncertainty. It operates across scales — from a single sign to a building-wide typographic system to a city's navigation infrastructure. This paper examines how environmental graphic design, spatial sequencing, and legibility decisions interact to either reduce or compound the disorientation of complex built environments.",
